class Solution {
public:
    int trailingZeroes(int n) {
        int count = 0;
        for (int i = 5; n / i >= 1; i *= 5) {
            count += n / i;
        }
        return count;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iteratively counts the multiples of 5, 25, 125, and so on, within the range of n!. Each multiple of 5 contributes one trailing zero to the factorial.  This logarithmic approach efficiently determines the count without iterating through all the numbers in n!.

